Represent the ticket sales over these two days by the matrix \( M = \begin{pmatrix} 120 & 95 & 30 & 135 & 140 & 25 \\ 145 & 120 & 20 & 150 & 130 & 18 \end{pmatrix} \). (i) Write a 3 \times 1 matrix, \( C \), representing the costs: $12 for adults, $8 for children, and $6 for seniors. (ii) Find the matrix \( T = MC \). (iii) Explain what each of the elements of matrix \( T \) represents. (iv) Determine the total revenue from ticket sales for both days.
